This article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Barack Obama on October 17, 2014. The memorandum provides an order of succession within the Federal Mediation and Conciliation Service (FMCS). According to the memorandum, in the event that the Director of FMCS is unable to perform their duties, the following officials will act as and perform the functions of the Director in the listed order: (a) Deputy Director, Mediation Services and Field Programs, (b) Deputy Director, National and International Programs, (c) Director of Field Operations, and (d) Most senior Director of Mediation Services. The memorandum also includes exceptions and general provisions, and the President retains discretion to depart from the memorandum in designating an acting Director. The memorandum is intended to provide clarity on the order of succession within FMCS and does not create any enforceable rights or benefits.